Direct Known Subclasses:
Enumerator, ForwardingFluentList, ForwardingFluentMap, ForwardingFluentSet
public abstract class AbstractEnumerable<E>
extends Object
implements Enumerable<E>

Default implementation of Enumerable. The only method left for subclasses to implement is iterator.

Description copied from interface: Enumerable
Similar to Enumerable.map(Object), but returns a list where the elements are pairs whose first element is the element from the Enumerable, and the second one is the result of the closure applied to such element. If you want a Map, just use Enumerable.toMap() afterwards, or just use the convenience method Enumerable.toMapBy(Object) instead.
